title: Google\Cloud\Compute\V1\CacheKeyPolicy
name: CacheKeyPolicy
description:
Message containing what to include in the cache key for a request for Cloud CDN.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.compute.v1.CacheKeyPolicy

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.include_host
params.description: If true, requests to different hosts will be cached separately.

params.name: data.include_protocol
params.description: If true, http and https requests will be cached separately.

params.name: data.include_query_string
params.description: If true, include query string parameters in the cache key according to query_string_whitelist and query_string_blacklist. If neither is set, the entire query string will be included. If false, the query string will be excluded from the cache key entirely.

params.name: data.query_string_blacklist
params.description: Names of query string parameters to exclude in cache keys. All other parameters will be included. Either specify query_string_whitelist or query_string_blacklist, not both. '&' and '=' will be percent encoded and not treated as delimiters.

params.name: data.query_string_whitelist
params.description: Names of query string parameters to include in cache keys. All other parameters will be excluded. Either specify query_string_whitelist or query_string_blacklist, not both. '&' and '=' will be percent encoded and not treated as delimiters.
